# DashDraft Analytics - Environment Variables Configuration

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. FRONTEND ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (Vite Bundled)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Used in the React web application for tracking pageviews, documentation opened,
# GitHub links opened, and installation copy/button clicks.
# This variable is public and is compiled into the static frontend assets.
VITE_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. NETLIFY FUNCTION ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (Server-side Private Keys)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Used in serverless Netlify Functions to dispatch events directly to GA4
# via the Measurement Protocol when users trigger download curl/powershell scripts.
# Define these directly inside the Netlify dashboard (Site settings -> Environment variables).
# Keep GA_API_SECRET confidential.

# GA4 Measurement ID (must match VITE_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID)
GA_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# GA4 API Secret generated in GA4 console:
# Admin -> Data Streams -> select your Web stream -> Measurement Protocol API secrets -> Create
GA_API_SECRET=your_measurement_protocol_api_secret_here
